The invention discloses an electronic map scaling display method. The method comprises the following steps of: setting a map picture with multiple levels of scaling ratios; dividing the map picture with multiple levels of scaling ratios into multiple bitmaps with corresponding scaling ratios; identifying the bitmaps with different scaling ratios by use of the ratio variable record; obtaining the information; searching for and loading the bitmap with the required scaling ratio according to the information and the ratio variable record to perform combination and piecing together; and displaying a complete map picture with the scaling ratio level by level in a fade-in fade-out manner. The method disclosed by the invention can perform scaling display of the map picture in an undistorted, smooth and more humanized manner so as to eliminate the rigid feeling of the traditional scaling method, and also can greatly improve the visual effect and experience of the user. The electronic map scaling display method disclosed by the invention is widely applied to the field of real-time monitoring.
