The invention discloses a monitoring system which comprises a monitoring center and a plurality of vehicular monitoring devices connected by a mobile network. Each vehicular monitoring device is provided with a video acquiring module, a positioning module and a wireless transmission module, wherein the video acquiring module is used for monitoring a vehicle key position in real time and converting monitored information into vehicular video data including a static image and/or dynamic video; the positioning module is used for monitoring the vehicle position in real time and marching/stopping states of a vehicle to generate a vehicle positioning data; the wireless transmission module is used for sending the vehicle video data and the vehicle positioning data; and the monitoring center is used for monitoring the vehicle in real time according to the vehicle video data and the vehicle positioning data. The vehicular monitoring device provided by the invention is provided with a positioning module which can be used for monitoring the vehicle position and the marching/stopping states of the vehicle to generate the vehicle positioning data in real time, therefore, the vehicle can be monitored efficiently, pertinently and promptly.

